# Gas Town Codebase - AI Assistant Guide

## Overview
This is a Gas Town implementation - a multi-agent orchestration system for coordinating AI coding agents. Start with `.ai/context/overview.md`.

## When Asked About
- **Architecture**: Read `.ai/context/architecture.md`
- **Domain terms**: Check `.ai/context/glossary.md`
- **Specific feature**: Look up in `.ai/maps/component-map.json`
- **Commands**: Check `internal/cmd/` and `.ai/maps/component-map.json`

## When Modifying Code
- **Adding features**: Follow `.ai/guides/adding-features.md`
- **Common tasks**: See `.ai/guides/common-tasks.md`
- **CLI commands**: Create in `internal/cmd/`, register in `init()`, add to command group
- **Agent roles**: Create template in `internal/templates/roles/`, manager in `internal/<role>/`

## Code Patterns
- CLI uses Cobra framework (`internal/cmd/`)
- Managers handle business logic (`internal/<component>/manager.go`)
- Types defined in `types.go` files
- Tests mirror source structure with `*_test.go` files
- Two-level beads architecture: town-level (hq-*) vs rig-level (project prefix)

## Repository Structure
- Source code: Clean, no AI-specific comments
- AI context: Everything in `.ai/` directory
- Human docs: `docs/` for user-facing documentation
- Commands: `internal/cmd/` for CLI
- Components: `internal/<component>/` for business logic

## Key Concepts
- **Town**: Workspace root (`~/gt/`) coordinating all workers
- **Rig**: Project container wrapping a git repository
- **Beads**: Git-backed atomic work units (JSONL format)
- **Convoy**: Work-order wrapping related beads
- **Hook**: Special pinned bead for each agent (GUPP principle)
- **Identity**: All work attributed to agents (e.g., `gastown/crew/joe`)

## Agent Roles
- **Mayor**: Town-level coordinator
- **Deacon**: Background supervisor daemon
- **Witness**: Per-rig polecat lifecycle manager
- **Refinery**: Per-rig merge queue processor
- **Polecat**: Ephemeral worker agent
- **Crew**: Persistent worker agent
- **Dog**: Cross-rig infrastructure worker

## Important Principles
- **GUPP**: If work is on your hook, you must run it
- **MEOW**: Molecular Expression of Work - decompose into trackable units
- **NDI**: Nondeterministic Idempotence - ensure eventual completion
- **Identity**: All work must be attributed to specific agents
- **Two-level beads**: Town-level (hq-*) for coordination, rig-level for implementation
